<item>
            <title>[JCR-1485] Introduce daily integration test suite</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1485</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>Some time ago we discussed integration tests that would be run on a daily basis. See also comments in issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1452&quot; title=&quot;Make use of jackrabbit.test.scale in test cases&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-1452&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. It seems we reached consensus that running a daily integration test suite is desirable.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Here&amp;#39;s my proposal:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- Introduce a test suite org.apache.jackrabbit.core.integration.daily.DailyIntegrationTest which includes all tests that should be run on a daily basis.&lt;br/&gt;
- Configure our continuous integration system to run the test suite on a daily basis. e.g. mvn -Dtest=DailyIntegrationTest package&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
With this approach we don&amp;#39;t need to introduce maven profiles or any other pom magic, yet it&amp;#39;s easy for a developer to run the daily tests when needed.</description>
